The paper discusses the role of LPWAN in the cellular IoT infrastructure, which falls under the category of networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also presents a performance analysis of LPWAN systems, which involves information theory and communication technology (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper speculates on the characteristics of coming IoT applications, which could be related to machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.MA). The paper also discusses potential enhancements to current technologies, which could involve system engineering and control (cs.SY) and security and cryptography (cs.CR).
